<font color="#FF0000">STIMULI - PARTY POOPERS</font><br>
<tt>Wed Oct 29 10:32:14 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Shot a large Jersey bull..farmer began to complain.  When I reached for my P-38 he joined me in marveling that it was the biggest spike buck he had ever seen.<br><br>
I have found that hunting is an activity that pushes a few buttons in my head.  The stealth.. rifle.. poor visibility at dawn and dusk.. the anticipation.. the silence.. the feeling that you are being watched.  If I had not ingrained a deep love for the woods and hunting as a child, I wonder if I could pull it off now.  My deceased brother sold his rifles when he returned from RVN.<br>
Followed a blood trail for a 1000 meters (shot ole big boy high in the ribs.)  Felt a brief flood of shame that rolled over my delight at bagging a buck.. Thanked the Creator for this animal who will grace my table.  Could it be that the evil residuals of war have contaminated every facet of my simple existence?  Is this annual hunting venture to be a joyful challenge and pleasant distraction or will it be a mercurial rize from delight to dispair?  <br>
I can't stop going to Wal-Mart just because children cry and raise hell for being denied something in the toy department.. (crying children devastates me!)<br>
I choose to face stimuli straight up.. if I get my ass kicked.. I gain some ground.. if I run I am destined to know fear forever.<br>
Perhaps there is something to be shared in discussing the stimuli that triggers our emotions.  Might make a good topic.<br><br>
MTF<br><br>
P.S.  Funny... I feel no remorse in abusing Cookie!<br><br>

<p><code>-- Just Me!  (the way I am) </code><p>


